> > "Albert D. Cahalan" <acahalan@cs.uml.edu> said:
>
> >> Long term, I think the whole core file idea needs to be tossed in
> >> favor of just starting a debugger.
[ arguments pro and con deleted ]
How about starting up a debugger on the faulting process, and
making the default "debugger" be a simple core-dumper?  The 
core-dumper could be configured to generate whatever file 
name you want, and the kernel wouldn't have to know anything 
about core files at all.
